# LBP Image Processor

Application for processing PGM images using Local Binary Patterns (LBP), by Erick Oliveira Arnou.


## Requirements

- Python 3.x
- C compiler (gcc)
- xdg-open (for automatic image viewing on Linux)


## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone [your-repository-url]
   cd [repository-name]


## Running
1. Place your .pgm P5 image in /src/datas/inputs/ directory
2. In root directory, Run: Python3 run.py <Your-PGM-Archive-Placed-In-'Inputs/'>
